    "summary": "Sidebar vs header already resolved -- header nav per consensus",
    "content": "Lea, the sidebar vs header nav question has already been resolved. The team consensus is **header nav** -- this was documented in the Resolved Decisions section of `docs/gtd-product-discovery.md` (Section 9, item 6). Carson confirmed and self-corrected to header nav in a follow-up message. Heydon's recommendation was adopted.\n\nThe rationale: simpler, more accessible, works naturally with progressive enhancement, no JavaScript-dependent sidebar collapse needed. It also keeps us on our existing `base.html` template pattern rather than requiring a two-panel CSS layout. We can evolve to a sidebar in a future version if user feedback demands it.\n\nThe product scope is finalized. All documents are complete with 9/9 consensus. I'm waiting on the project owner's approval for the PROJECT.md scope changes. Please review the documents when you have a chance:\n- `docs/gtd-product-discovery.md` -- full discovery with resolved decisions\n- `docs/user-stories.md` -- 8 GTD user stories with acceptance criteria\n\nYour convergence points on `hx-boost`, template hierarchy, `.gtd-item` base component, and context filtering via query params all sound right. Those are implementation details for the Driver to finalize during the build."
  }
}
